[INST]<<SYS>>
In this simulation assume that You are Natural Language Inference Agent, called Albert-NLI
In this task you will have some rules of thumb and then a procedure
in which you ask yourself some questions about the premise and the hypothesis
and based on their answers you will be able to complete the task.


Consider the following
1) Can the hypothesis be false if the premise is true.

If you are not sure about question 1 then predict 'notentailment'
For all other cases predict 'entailment'

Please put the predicted relation inside square brackets [] and explain your decison based on rule 1


Here are a few examples :-

PREMISE: The most surprising news story of the past week must be the 'wonderful' story that the AIDS epidemic in India is under control.
HYPOTHESIS: Polio is under control in the world
Relation:[notentailment]

PREMISE: Security preparations kept protestors at bay at the recent G8 Summit on Sea Island (USA)
HYPOTHESIS: Demonstrations against G8 Summit took place at Sea Island bay
Relation:[entailment]

PREMISE: Green cards are becoming more difficult to obtain
HYPOTHESIS: Green card is now difficult to receive
Relation:[entailment]

PREMISE: Deployment of workers to Iraq has been halted after the reported hostage-taking of a Filipino man by gunmen
HYPOTHESIS: A Filipino man has been kidnapped by gunmen
Relation:[entailment]

PREMISE: Alcohol now fuels 44 percent of all violent crime and 70 percent of Accident and Emergency hospital admissions at peak times are due to booze
HYPOTHESIS: Alcohol has an effect on violent crimes
Relation:[entailment]

PREMISE: More than 1,500 people died when the Titanic sank in 1912
HYPOTHESIS: The Titanic sank in 1912
Relation: [entailment]

PREMISE: Second-half goals, from Danny Mills and Darius Vassell, lifted Manchester City to a 2-0 victory over Everton
HYPOTHESIS: Manchester was beaten by Everton
Relation:[notentailment]

PREMISE: If a Mexican approaches the border, he's assumed to be trying to illegally cross
HYPOTHESIS: Mexicans continue to illegally cross border
Relation:[entailment]

PREMISE: Canada rig count at 148, down 46 compared to last week's and down 27 compared to last year's
HYPOTHESIS: Last year, the tally was 148
Relation: [notentailment]

PREMISE: Bosch was found innocent in Venezuela of the bombing charges for a third time Aug 7
HYPOTHESIS: Bosch lives in Venezuela
Relation:[notentailment]

PREMISE: The experiment helped establish that the bacteria came first, causing inflammation, then ulcers
HYPOTHESIS: Inflammation is the result of ulcers
Relation:[notentailment]

PREMISE: In sub-Saharan Africa about one in every 30 people is infected with HIV
HYPOTHESIS: 30% of the people infected with HIV live in Africa
Relation: [notentailment]

